$this->content->template['plugin']['google_sitemap']['text3'] = "<p><b>changefreq:</b> <br />The frequency, with which the side will presumably change. This value gives general information to search machines. It does not stand necessarily with the frequency in connection, with which you scan the side. Valid values are:<br /> "; 
$this->content->template['plugin']['google_sitemap']['text4'] = "The value &quot;always&quot; is used for the description of documents, which change at each access. The value &quot;never&quot; is for the description of archived URLs.<br /><br />The value of this tag is considered as advice, not as command. The search engine crawlers consider these informations at their decisions indeed, but they may browse sites marked as &quot;hourly&quot; more seldom as hourly, as they may browse sites marked as &quot;yearly&quot; more often than yearly. Even sites marked as &quot;never&quot; may be browsed by such crawlers in certain time intervals to recognize unexpected changes on these sites.<br /></p><p><b>Priority:</b><br />The priority of this URL compared to other URLs on your Website. Valid values are between 0.0 and 1.0. This value does not influence the comparision of your site with other websites, it only lets the search engine crawlers know which (sub-) sites are the most important to you. The priority that you give to one of your sites is used by the search engines only for a selection between URLs of one and the same website. The use of this tag increases the likelihood that your more important sites are listed in the search index.<br /><br />Just as little is it useful to tag the highest priority to all URLs on your website. As the priority is relative, it is used only for the selection between URLs on your own website. The priority on your website is not compared to the priority on other websites.<br /><br /></p>"; 
